# Streamlit secrets template — how the deployed app authenticates.
#
# LOCAL: a real ".streamlit/secrets.toml" is optional (it's git-ignored); the
#        .env file already works for `streamlit run`.
# CLOUD: on Streamlit Community Cloud, put the two lines below — with REAL
#        values — into the app's  Settings -> Secrets  box, then Save.
#
# The GCP key is supplied as ONE base64 line (TOML-safe: no braces/newlines/
# quotes to break the parser). Generate the real value in PowerShell:
#
#   $b64 = [Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("Project_123.json"))
#   "GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_B64 = `"$b64`""    # prints the line to copy
#
# (QDRANT_API_KEY is the value from your .env. GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT is optional —
#  the app reads project_id from inside the decoded key.)

QDRANT_API_KEY = "your-qdrant-cloud-api-key"
GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_B64 = "base64-of-your-entire-service-account-json"
